Articles from Britannica encyclopedias for elementary and high school students.Ehud Barak - Student Encyclopedia (Ages 11 and up)(born 1942). When Ehud Brog became an army recruit at the age of 18, he changed his name from one of European derivation to one in Hebrew. His new name, Barak, meant "lightning." In his 35-year military career, Barak rose to the post of chief of staff, Israel’s highest rank, and became the most decorated soldier in the nation’s history. After making the transition to politics in 1995, he distinguished himself again as a strong-willed leader, and four years later he became prime minister of Israel.
